<br>
Now let me make this clear I ENJOY HELPING.  Some of you should know that and I hope that all will eventually.<br>
<br>
Trade seemed to be going on uneventfully we transfer some pp then Shriekra suggests we hunt together and would i mind transfering some equipment as well.  I think great i could really use the company as it looked like solosville for me that night. Sure np I was just gonna shop a little anyway, so Shriekra comes back gives me 2 items and even offers a weapon upgrade to me which I did turn down but very generous of her to offer.  She then logged her alt back in and i put the 2 items in trade window and hit trade.  She then says what about the tunic after the trade goes through.. I say I gave it too you she said no seriously con't fool around ..I'm not I dont have it.  Well let me tell u this item was a fungi tunic by all reports a 100,000pp item.  I was in shock what do we do? Let's petition she said.   She then petitioned and I did as well. There was a guide on in quenyos at 7:10ish right after this happened.  I took a screen shot of the trade and then we sat and waited Shreikra eventually logged her alt off at i think like 10ish and i logged at 11:15 or so no reply the whole time.  I then sent a feedback on top of my petition and this morning contacted a gm through eq live website customer support and I am waiting for a reply.  By the way i don't think i mentioned it but Shreikra was a true gentlemen/lady (whichever is behind her avatar) throughout this. <br>
<br>
I feel responsible for the tremendous loss that Shreikra suffered and have no way of making up for it myself.  This I do vow tho, if Verant doesn't return the Tunic to Shreikra or myself so that I can return it to her, I will do everything in my power to both replace it in game and to make VI's reputation suffer for it.  In an online game such as Everquest the experience is about interacting with people making friends in a setting that helps us escape from ordinary life.  It should be a fun, enjoyable thing.  Niether I or Shreikra deserve this headache.  I am concerned that it may place a strain on our budding friendship or on her desire to play this game.<br>
<br>
To Shreikra I give my sincerest apology, to Verant I give fair warning, make amends or face my wrath, to my brother and sister Arrows I ask for understanding and trust.<br>
<br>
